text: be careful not to drop any bits on the floor! it's lethal to dogs (learned from marce just now)
<http://www.petmd.com/dog/conditions/digestive/c_dg_salmon_poisoning_disease>

attachments.text: Salmon poisoning disease (SPD) is an often fatal condition, occurring when a dog eats raw salmon that is infected with the Neorickettsia helminthoeca parasite. This disease typically begins in the tissues of the small intestine, where it causes hemorrhaging. It gradually becomes systemic, invading the entire body.
